text: Crossotus subocellatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae. It was described by Fairmaire in 1886. It is known from Djibouti, Algeria, Chad, Senegal, Eritrea, Kenya, Egypt, Libya, Mali, Mauritania, Saudi Arabia, Ethiopia, Morocco, Oman, Niger, Nigeria, Somalia, Tunisia, Sudan, and the Western Sahara.BioLib.cz - Crossotus subocellatus. Retrieved on 8 September 2014. It feeds on Acacia tortilis. ==References== Category:Lamiinae Category:Beetles described in 1886
